g.text: Titus Hardie: "Easy, fellas, we got company," Titus puts an end to it. "Let's see what brings the cop around."
Visual Calculus: Too late to stop you. You've already got them all -- including the old bearded man who's smart enough to smoke instead of talking.
Theo: As you can see he doesn't speak a lot... and you almost missed him among the others.
Visual Calculus: Maybe. But hey, you've stood there for about four seconds, not saying anything. Now is a good time to hit them with questions -- where's the eighth Hardie?
Titus Hardie: "What are you talkin' about, madman? There's no eighth Hardie boy. There's seven of us and we're all here." He sizes you up.
Titus Hardie: "Or what -- *you* want to be the eighth Hardie boy? We ain't hiring!" He shakes his head.
Titus Hardie: "Shut the *fuck* up, Glen!" he roars. "I do the talking here! Now what the fuck do you want, cop?"
You: One of them is missing. The Odd Sole?
Visual Calculus: Exactly. You've stood there for about four seconds, not saying anything. Hit them with questions -- where's the eighth Hardie?
Visual Calculus: Of course. When you get the time, you could take another look at those tracks in the yard. See if they fit this band of miscreants.
Shanky: "Yeah, what brings you around, copper?" the rat-faced sycophant repeats.
Perception (Sight): Of the actors here. You could take another look at the tracks in the mud -- on the crime scene. Compare it to these guys.
Kim Kitsuragi: Variable["XP.figured_out_the_odd_sole"] == true and Variable["TASK.confront_hardie_about_drug_trade"] == false
Visual Calculus: Yes. Ruby the *lady driver drug runner*. There's no denying it now. Time to ask the boys some questions...
Theo: Sitting on his right: standard working boots, size 45 or 46. Eldest in the room, probably mid-fifties. Smoker, quiet.
Suggestion: ... use it to take a dig at his friend. Flood gates open.
Glen: "Yeah, Dennis, calm down," a blond man in his thirties agrees. "No one's fucking you, you stupid fuck."
Suggestion: Too late -- you already got a pretty good picture of these guys. You can use this.
Perception (Sight): Too late, you already scanned the room. You got a pretty good picture.
Fat Angus: "Yeah." The fat guy in the middle lets out a little chuckle. "You're not even being fucked, Dennis."
Eugene: "Relax, Dennis, no one is fucking you yet," says the forty-something man from the corner, with a plectrum hanging from his neck.
You: What can I use it for?
Jump to: [Titus Hardie: ""What are you talkin' about, madman..."]
Logic: It has to be good if he won't let you pursue it. Looks like the lieutenant thinks so too...
Kim Kitsuragi: "So let me get this straight... there *is* an eighth Hardie boy, it's a *she* and you don't like us talking about her?"
Alain: Across, at the other table: hobnailed working boots, size 43. Gang tattoos. Mesque or Saramirizian. In his late thirties/early forties.
Encyclopedia: He spent his youth in Villalobos, a housing project in the Jamrock Quarter. There were incarcerations. Hard to say what else -- the ink is fading.
Titus Hardie: "No-no-no," Titus points at himself, "Eyes here! You got business with my boys, you got business with me."
Logic: He understood what you were trying to do. Taking inventory of them.
Titus Hardie: "That's right, we're not talking about this. This is a private Hardie boys matter, nothing to do with your shit. *And*..." He points at the lieutenant.

Suggestion: Now watch the other guys fuck it up by falling out of line.
Shanky: "Yeah, you fuck with the Hardie boys, you fuck with Titus Hardie!" shouts the scrawny rat-faced man, two teeth missing in the front.
Visual Calculus: That's enough to take another look at those tracks in the yard. See if they fit this band of miscreants.
Alain: "Let Dennis enjoy his fucking, man. We don't mind." You notice gang tattoos; the man must be either Mesque or Saramirizian.
Titus Hardie: "The fuck is with you, fella?" Titus is staring at you with his head tilted.
Visual Calculus: Exactly. But none of this is news to you. You've stood there for about four seconds, not saying anything -- time to move on...
Fat Angus: In the middle, heaving and wheezing: big guy, boot size 46, deep marks. Probably carried the victim over. He alone is 130 kilos; add the man in armour and you could easily exceed 220.

In the middle, heaving and wheezing: The fabled giant of Koko Nur, boot size 46, deep marks. Probably carried the victim over. He alone is 130 kilos; add the man in armour and you could easily exceed 220.
Perception (Smell): Awful smell. His feet stink from all the way over there, despite having boots on.
Suggestion: You could take another look at the tracks in the yard, see if they fit with the characters here -- it could be incriminating.
You: Not necessarily. The lady driver could have kept the drug trade secret.
Glen: "Actually, boss, we've been talking and we think she could maybe..."
Glen: Starting from the right: Boot size 44. Blond man in his thirties. Overbearingly masculine.
Composure: Wants the world to know he's a macho-macho man: tobacco-chewing and knuckle cracking. Who else do we have here?
Shanky: Size 41, with the light step. Not a child after all -- an older man with a rat-face; mean watery eyes and two front teeth missing.
Suggestion: This one knows how to keep things going. He's a hothead, but not one to be taken lightly. The last one is a bit of a black sheep...
Glen: "Sorry, boss..." you hear the blond man almost whimper.
Pain Threshold: A symmetric burn on his neck, resembling the letters *Los Los*. Has he tried to burn it off, leave that life behind?

Titus Hardie: And then -- standard working boot, steel reinforced toes, size 46. The big dick. Wide at the shoulders and lean at the hips. Rugby cap, fingerless gloves, and numerous scars, a little under forty.
Eugene: On his neck. Forget it. It's not important.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Good -- we're all watching each other." The lieutenant adjusts his spectacles. "Officer, your question?"
Esprit de Corps: There's no point in pushing it further, he thinks. This is already a victory. We'll learn more about this eighth Hardie sooner or later.
Drama: Let's call this one The Musician.
Perception (Sight): Good. You could take another look at the tracks in the yard -- on the crime scene. See if they fit this bunch.
You: This would fit what Joyce told us, but I don't want to make any assumptions.
Titus Hardie: "You're not cops here. Don't go digging around, if you don't want a bullet in the back of your head. I'm watching you."
Visual Calculus: In conclusion: these seven are the actors on the crime scene. The footprints were theirs, but there's a *discrepancy*.
Suggestion: Yes, falling out of line to *please* him! This is the best kind. And now this guy is going to...
Suggestion: This person Glen wants to hire -- he really respects her.
Perception (Sight): The emblem on his vest says 'Rowing club'. A little patch below it reads: 'T. Hardie, Captain'.
Shanky: "Fuckin' say something already!" The rat-faced man doesn't let you think.
Shanky: "Fuckin' say something already!" The rat-faced man doesn't let you finish the thought.
You: "I found eight sets of footprints, but there's only seven of you... Where is the eighth Hardie boy?"
Reaction Speed: Hmmm... *She*? So there is an eighth Hardie and it's a Hardie girl?
Logic: It has to be good if he won't let you pursue it.
You: One of them is absent. The Odd Sole?
You: The entire Union might be involved. Maybe even all of Martinaise... (Look around suspiciously.)
Reaction Speed: *She*? So there is an eighth Hardie and it's a Hardie girl? Who might it be, Elizabeth the gardener?
Visual Calculus: Exactly, the missing lady driver who was running the drug trade. Does it mean that the Hardie boys are involved in the drug trade as well?
Eugene: In the far corner: standard working boot, steel reinforced toes, size 44. Forty-something, non-alcoholic beverage in hand. (You squint.) Is that a *plectrum*?
